# CODEOWNERS — path-based reviewer requirements
#
# Syntax: GitHub CODEOWNERS. Each line specifies a path pattern and the
# GitHub usernames or team handles who must review changes to that path.
# The last matching pattern takes precedence.
#
# Per GOVERNANCE.md merge policy:
#   - Security-critical paths require 2 of 3 reviewers from at least 2
#     distinct organizations.
#   - Other code paths require 1 maintainer + 1 contributor (or 2 maintainers).
#   - RFC, governance, license, and CODEOWNERS changes require RFC + Board.
#
# Maintainer placeholders below will be replaced with real handles as
# Phase 0 hires land. Until then, CODEOWNERS is enforced "best-effort" via
# the @promethea-os/maintainers team.

# Default owner — every file requires at least one maintainer review.
*                               @promethea-os/maintainers

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Security-critical paths — 2-of-3 reviewers from 2+ distinct organizations
# enforced via branch protection rules in GitHub settings.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

/services/privacy/              @promethea-os/privacy-leads @promethea-os/security-reviewers
/services/ota/                  @promethea-os/ota-leads     @promethea-os/security-reviewers
/services/push/                 @promethea-os/push-leads    @promethea-os/security-reviewers
/services/telemetry/            @promethea-os/privacy-leads @promethea-os/security-reviewers
/services/compliance/           @promethea-os/privacy-leads @promethea-os/security-reviewers
